\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. N. salzmannii} (Boiss.) Rouy,{\i  Fl. Fr.}{\b  14}: 301 (1913) ({\i Nardurus salzmannii} Boiss.). Stems up to 40 cm, slender, erect, rather rigid. Inflorescence 2-23 cm, rigid, rarely with a few branches; pedicels up to 0·5 mm. Spikelets (2·2-)4-7 mm, appressed, set in depressions in rhachis. Glumes broadly hyaline at margin; lower 1·5-2·7 mm, with (1-)3(-5) veins; upper 1·8-3·2 mm, with 3-5 veins. Lemma 2·2-3·2 mm, emarginate to shortly 2-fid, unawned but sometimes apiculate, glabrous. Rhachilla-segments 0·8-1·2 mm. 2n = 14.{\i  Dry places. S. & C. Spain; S.E. France.} Ga Hs.
