\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals. Leaves flat, convolute when dry. Inflorescence a raceme or sparingly branched panicle. Spikelets with 5-25 florets, disarticulating below each floret. Glumes subequal, weakly to strongly keeled, acute to obtuse. Lemma 5-veined, with 1-5 of the veins prominent, keeled to rounded on back, often with a short apiculum, coriaceous, acute to shortly 2-fid. Anthers 3, slightly exserted at anthesis. Grain 1·5-2 mm, ellipsoid-oblong, strongly adherent to palea, glabrous; hilum punctiform, sub-basal.
\par

\par

