\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. D. sicula} (Jacq.) Dumort.,{\i  Comment. Bot.} 27 (1822). Stems up to 25 cm, erect. Inflorescence 1·5-6 cm, not rigid, with spikelets on 2 sides, unbranched; pedicels 0·5-1 mm, appressed, stout. Spikelets 10-22 mm, ovate, crowded, with (5-)12-25 florets, tardily disarticulating. Glumes slightly unequal, keeled, obtuse to subacute, glabrous or aculeolate on midrib; lower glume 2·5-3 mm, 3-veined; upper glume 3-4 mm, 3- to 5-veined. Lemma 3·5-4·5 mm, strongly keeled, subacute to obtuse, not or very shortly apiculate, more or less cucullate, glabrous to sparsely aculeolate on keel, with minute capitate hairs near base. Rhachilla-segments c. 0·7 mm, with minute capitate hairs. Anthers 0·8-1·4 mm.{\i  Dry places. S. Spain, Sardegna, S. Italy, Sicilia.} Hs It Sa Si.
\par

